Messages.Value: Thank you for calling. This is Elijah. How may I assist you today?
Hi Elijah. This is John Smith. I'm having some trouble accessing my booking confirmation for my recent trip from New York to Los Angeles.
I'm sorry to hear that, John. Let me assist you with that. Can you please provide me with your booking reference number?
Yes, it's ABC123. My flight was on January 20th, 2022.
Thank you for that information, John. Let me check that for you.
I see that your booking confirmation was sent to your email address. Can you please check your spam folder or double-check that it's the correct email address?
I've already checked all my folders and it's not there. Can you just resend it to me?

I'm sorry John, but I can't resend it to you because I don't have access to the system right now. However, I can confirm that your booking is confirmed and active. You can show your travel itinerary to the airport staff, and they will assist you.
What do you mean you can't resend it? Isn't that your job? I've been on hold for so long and now you're telling me you can't even help me? This is ridiculous!

I apologize for the inconvenience, John. I understand you're upset, and I assure you that I'm doing everything I can to assist you. Unfortunately, I'm unable to resend the confirmation email right now. However, I will log a ticket and follow up with you as soon as possible to get this resolved. Is there anything else I can help you with today?
No, that's all. Thank you for your help.
